# Job Copilot — non-negotiable guardrails

These override any instinct to make the tool more powerful or more automatic. They apply to every session.

1. **Sanctioned sources only.** Automatic discovery ONLY from Greenhouse, Lever, and Ashby public read APIs. NEVER build a scraper or automated login/submit against LinkedIn or Indeed. A manually pasted LinkedIn/Indeed URL may be fetched once as plain text (reading a page), but such postings are marked `sourceRestricted = true`, which blocks the automated submit path — hand off to the user with an "open this page and click Submit yourself" action.
2. **No fabrication in résumés.** Tailoring may only reword, reorder, and re-emphasize content already in the base résumé. NEVER add an employer, title, date, skill, or metric that isn't in the base. Every tailored résumé runs the fabrication check against `Resume.baseFacts`; anything new is flagged in RED on the review screen.
3. **Human approval by default.** Nothing leaves the machine (email send, portal submit) without an explicit Approve click. Any "auto-send after N minutes" toggle defaults to OFF.
4. **Stop at CAPTCHAs and logins.** Browser automation must detect CAPTCHA / unfamiliar login walls, pause, surface a "your turn" notice, and resume only on user confirmation. NEVER attempt to solve or bypass a challenge.
5. **Local-first & private.** Résumés, personal details, and credentials stay on the machine. SQLite + `.env`. The `.env` file and the SQLite database are gitignored — never commit secrets or the database.
